h3. Issue Summary
When using the *JIRA Issue* macro, if you set it to be displayed as a 'Table', the *JIRA Links* option gets hidden on the page. If you let it displaying as 'Single issue', it shows as the expected.

h3. Environment
* Cloud;
* Both editing experiences.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new page on Confluence;
# Add the *JIRA Issue* macro;
# Insert a simple JQL on the filter (like 'key = jira_issue-number');
# On the macro pop-up, click on *Display options* and set the 'Table' option - under the _Display as_ section_;
# Insert the macro;
# Publish the page.

h3. Expected Results
On the published page, it is displayed the JIRA Links option, with the total amount of JIRA issues in the page.

h3. Actual Results
The JIRA Links is *hidden*.

h3. Notes
* When reproducing the steps, access the developer tools of your browser and search for the object {{content-metadata-jira}} - it is greyed out in the code, as well as the JIRA Link item. That's why it is hidden;
* In the 4th step, instead of choosing 'Table', change it to 'Single issue': the JIRA Links option will appear and the same above object is not hidden.


h3. Workaround
Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

